      VALUES ("Many people prefer to play  Abaddon as a support.And this is true,he is one of the best supports in the game,with great measure. He is one of the best in this role,possesing a heal that is also a nuke,a shield that blocks incomming damage,reflects it after the cap is reached,REMOVES DEBUFFS,has a passive that slows and allows allies to hit harder certain enemies(by certain I mean ones that were hit by  Abaddon before,and an AMASING ultimate that allows you to heal instead of taking damage.", "You should focus on helping your carry last hit,by occasionally casting  Aphotic Shield on him,or on the creep that is tanking the other wave,as the shield would burst unsuspectingly.Usage of death coil should be minimised in early game,as you take damage from using it,although you might use it to burst your  Aphotic Shield(if cast on yourself)", "You should be involved in every fight that occures,raking up that assist gold everywhere. Borrowed Time will make you durable,so try to sacrifice your life for your carry,as most of times,you will both escape(lol then how did you sacrifice). Mekansm+ Urn of Shadows+death coil can instantly revigorate any wounded teammate.", "Keep up the good work.Now that you are more durable,you can actually run head first into teamfights or play the role of a bait.Your healing/protecting combo still helps in teamfights,and your extreme durability will turn the tide of fights in your favor,mostly due to  Borrowed Time.", "Versatility in one word (Support)", "dotafire", "Wulfstan", "http://www.dotafire.com/dota-2/guide/versatility-in-one-word-abaddon-3935","Abaddon", "55");
